        public IllegalArgumentException invalidScheme(URI uri,
                                              String expectedScheme)
        Creates an exception that can be thrown if a URI (e.g. used for FileSystemProvider.getPath(URI)) has an invalid scheme.
        Parameters:
        uri - The URI with the invalid scheme.
        expectedScheme - The expected scheme.
        Returns:
        The created exception.

      • notHierarchical

        public IllegalArgumentException notHierarchical(URI uri)

        Parameters:

        The created exception.
